Whenever we add a new keyboard layer, we need to also update the encoder map to
ensure it has the same number of entries. When all encoder layers have
identical mappings, the encoder map array is redundant.

One possible solution is to replace the `encoder_map` array and
`ENCODER_MAP_ENABLE` with an `encoder_update_user()` function:

```c
bool encoder_update_user(uint8_t index, bool clockwise) {
    if (index == 0) {
        tap_code16(clockwise ? KC_BRIU : KC_BRID);
    } else {
        tap_code16(clockwise ? KC_VOLU : KC_VOLD);
    }
    return false;
}
```

If per-layer encoder behavior is needed later, this approach still works — just
switch on `get_highest_layer(layer_state)` inside the function.